                <p>In <gloss target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss> 486 to Manila, May 24, approved by Mr.
                    Griffin, the <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> stated that the Budget Bureau
                    had granted the agency’s appeal for $35.4 million in grant aid [on a date
                    unspecified] and continued in part: “These funds are illustrative and at present
                    confidential and Phils cannot consider this firm amount even after Congressional
                    appropriations. These funds to be considered fluid within Asia and Pacific total
                    area request of $375 millions, but we believe will be completely available grant
                    programming on suitable fiscal ’52 projects. Actual amount on loan basis through
                    ExIm Bank not determined as yet but policies for integration being worked out
                    and formal note to Phil Govt in process.… this … is for your information and
                    cannot be transmitted to Phil Govt at this time.” (<gloss target="#t_ECA1"
                        >ECA</gloss> Cable Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> Lot 53 A
                    278)</p>
